    <note>Chen(1) Tong [7129] Grandson of Jiang [28], who was probably Wei's [96] brother. Dongzhi's [3091] son, Yangong's father [102], Si's [86] and Mu's [3077] elder brother, Yanwu's [103] uncle. Liang(1) Kuan's [7284], Lin(1) Ding's [7289] and Liu(2) Fangshan's [7292], father-in-law. According to Liu Ban's funerary inscription, Tong was orphaned at the age of 13 and moved to Suzhou, residence of his mother, Fang(1) furen. Even though some other sources date the move with his grandfather, Jiang, his brother and their descendants are al still listed as Putian, not Wuxian, jinshi. See also documentation for grandfather, Jiang. Fujian TZ, 147.20a; YLDD, 3145, 18a- 20a. CBD, 3, 2449.</note>
